```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as "Client Application"
    participant Server as "Server Application"
    participant AP as "Authentication Provider"

    note "Client initiates REST API call to Server"
    Client->>Server: POST /api/data HTTP/1.1
    alt "Client is authenticated"
        Client->>AP: Auth request for token
        AP->>Client: Token response
        Client->>Server: Authorization: Bearer <token>
        Server->>Server: Validate token
        alt "Token is valid"
            Server->>Server: Process request
            Server->>Client: Response
        else "Token is invalid"
            Server->>Server: Return 401 Unauthorized
        end
    else "Client is not authenticated"
        Server->>Client: Return 401 Unauthorized
    end
```

In this sequence diagram, the client application initiates a POST request to the server. The client is either authenticated or not, and the server handles the request accordingly. The authentication provider is used to authenticate the client.